{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016Rph3EB9cvAC8vKGGoQu3m","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have a complete understanding of the web UI code. Let me create a comprehensive final report.\n\n## Web UI Exploration Report - Cloche Project\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's a comprehensive summary of the web UI code structure and workflow visualization:\n\n### 1. **Web UI File Locations**\n\n**Directory Structure:**\n```\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/\n├── handler.go              (Main web server - 1,300+ lines)\n├── handler_stream_test.go\n├── handler_test.go\n├── static/\n│   └── style.css          (600 lines, complete styling)\n└── templates/\n    ├── layout.html         (Master template - 20 lines)\n    ├── projects.html       (Projects overview - 38 lines)\n    ├── runs.html           (Runs table with filtering - 170 lines)\n    ├── run_detail.html     (Run execution details - 355 lines)\n    └── project_detail.html (Project with workflow DAG - 315 lines)\n```\n\n**Total web UI code: ~1,500 lines across templates, CSS, and handler logic**\n\n### 2. **Workflow Graph Rendering - Current Implementation**\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (Lines 160-246)\n\n**Graph Rendering Approach:**\n- **Method:** Pure client-side SVG generation (no external library)\n- **Language:** Vanilla JavaScript embedded in HTML template\n- **Layout Algorithm:** Single-column vertical topological sort with fixed-width nodes\n- **Data Format:** JSON from API endpoint\n\n**Layout Engine Details:**\n\n```\nFixed dimensions:\n- nodeH = 48 (node height)\n- nodeW = 180 (node width)\n- gapY = 24 (vertical gap between nodes)\n- gapX = 40 (horizontal gap between node and edge)\n- padTop = 20 (top padding)\n- padLeft = 30 (left padding)\n\nPosition calculation:\n- X position: fixed at padLeft (30px)\n- Y position: padTop + index * (nodeH + gapY)\n- All nodes in a single column\n```\n\n### 3. **SVG Generation Details**\n\n**Elements rendered:**\n1. **Arrowhead marker** - defined in SVG defs with polygon\n2. **Wiring edges** - cubic Bezier curves connecting nodes\n3. **Edge labels** - step result names positioned above curves\n4. **Step nodes** - rectangles with rounded corners\n5. **Terminal nodes** - rounded rectangles for \"done\" and \"abort\" steps\n6. **Icons** - Unicode emoji placed in nodes:\n   - `🧠` (U+1F916) for agent steps\n   - `🔁` (U+1F501) for workflow steps\n   - `📋` (U+1F4DC) for script steps\n\n**SVG Classes defined in CSS:**\n- `.dag-svg` - container styling\n- `.dag-node-rect` - node rectangle styling\n- `.dag-node-text` - node label text\n- `.dag-edge` - connection line styling\n- `.dag-edge-label` - result label styling\n- `.dag-terminal-done` / `.dag-terminal-abort` - terminal node colors\n\n### 4. **API Endpoints for Workflow Data**\n\n**Endpoint:** `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n\n**Handler:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (Lines 1102-1220)\n\n**Response JSON Structure:**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"develop\",\n  \"file\": \".cloche/develop.cloche\",\n  \"location\": \"container\" | \"host\",\n  \"entry_step\": \"implement\",\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"implement\",\n      \"type\": \"agent\" | \"script\" | \"workflow\",\n      \"results\": [\"success\", \"fail\"],\n      \"config\": {\n        \"prompt\": \"file(prompts/implement.md)\",\n        \"max_attempts\": \"3\"\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"wires\": [\n    {\n      \"from\": \"implement\",\n      \"result\": \"success\",\n      \"to\": \"done\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### 5. **JavaScript Code Organization**\n\n**project_detail.html JavaScript functions:**\n\n1. **Data Loading:**\n   - `loadProjectInfo()` - fetches project metadata\n   - `loadWorkflows()` - loads and parses workflow data\n\n2. **Layout & Rendering:**\n   - `renderWorkflowTabs()` - creates tab buttons for multiple workflows\n   - `showWorkflow(wf)` - main SVG generation function\n   - `showFilteredWorkflow(idx)` - applies workflow filters\n\n3. **Graph Construction:**\n   - Topological sort via depth-first traversal from `entry_step`\n   - Position calculation via iterative Y-coordinate assignment\n   - Edge calculation using cubic Bezier curves\n   - Edge label placement at curve midpoints\n\n4. **Interactivity:**\n   - `openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)` - side panel showing step details\n   - `closeDrawer()` - closes step detail panel\n   - Click handlers on step nodes to open details\n\n### 6. **Graph Layout Algorithm (Pseudocode)**\n\n```javascript\n// 1. Topological Sort\nordered = []\nvisited = {}\nvisit(entryStep)  // DFS from entry\n// Add unvisited steps\n\n// 2. Position Assignment\npositions = {}\nordered.forEach((name, i) => {\n    positions[name] = {\n        x: padLeft,\n        y: padTop + i * (nodeH + gapY)\n    }\n})\n// Also position terminal nodes (done/abort)\n\n// 3. SVG Generation\n// Draw cubic Bezier edges\nwires.forEach(wire => {\n    x1 = from.x + nodeW\n    y1 = from.y + nodeH/2\n    x2 = to.x\n    y2 = to.y + nodeH/2\n    cx = x1 + gapX/2\n    path = cubic_bezier(x1,y1 → cx,y1 → cx,y2 → x2,y2)\n})\n\n// Draw nodes and labels\n```\n\n### 7. **Supporting UI Components**\n\n**run_detail.html (355 lines):**\n- Step execution table with collapsible output rows\n- Live log viewer via Server-Sent Events (SSE)\n- Real-time status updates via polling\n- Container state management buttons\n\n**runs.html (170 lines):**\n- Global runs table with parent-child hierarchy visualization\n- Project filtering dropdown\n- Run grouping logic (parents de-emphasized, children prominent)\n- Tree-style indentation for child runs\n\n**projects.html (38 lines):**\n- Project cards grid layout\n- Health status indicators (colored dots)\n- Recent run history (colored dots for state)\n- Quick links to project details\n\n### 8. **CSS Styling**\n\n**Complete styling** in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (600 lines):\n\n- **Theme colors:** Light/dark mode with CSS custom properties\n- **Badge states:** pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled, stopped\n- **Layout:** Container max-width 1100px, responsive grid layouts\n- **Components:** Panels, tabs, drawers, buttons, tables, badges\n- **DAG-specific:** Node rectangles, edges, edge labels, terminal nodes\n- **Animations:** Pulse effect for running states\n\n### 9. **Key Files Summary**\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | 1,300+ | Go HTTP handlers, template rendering, API endpoints |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` | 315 | DAG visualization (lines 160-246), workflow tabs, drawer |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` | 600 | All styling including DAG classes |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` | 355 | Step table, log viewer, SSE streaming |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` | 170 | Runs table, project filtering, run grouping |\n\n### 10. **Layout Engine Characteristics**\n\n**Current Approach:**\n- ✓ Single-column vertical layout\n- ✓ Fixed node dimensions\n- ✓ Simple topological sort for ordering\n- ✓ Cubic Bezier curves for edges\n- ✓ No overlapping nodes\n- ✓ Automatic SVG size calculation\n- ✓ Responsive to content\n\n**Limitations:**\n- No hierarchical/multi-level layout\n- No horizontal spacing optimization\n- No edge crossing minimization\n- Fixed node positions (Y-coordinate only)\n- No zoom/pan capabilities\n- No dynamic repositioning\n\n### 11. **Related Go Code**\n\n**Domain Model:** `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`\n- `Workflow` struct with Steps and Wiring\n- `Step` struct with Name, Type, Results, Config\n- `Wire` struct with From, Result, To, OutputMap\n\n**API Handler:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n- Parses `.cloche/*.cloche` and `.cloche/host.cloche` files\n- Serializes to JSON for client consumption\n- Serves step content files on demand\n\nAll web UI code is **embedded** in the Go binary via `//go:embed` directive, so there are no external dependencies on separate HTML/CSS/JS files at runtime."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aae3c1247625e8c29 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 55086\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 42984</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c63b3e9-21a0-4a0c-87f3-97db17cd05ef","uuid":"8197c591-7e66-486b-847c-eabd9a94473e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the web UI code in this project. I need to understand:\n1. Where the web UI files are located (HTML, JS, CSS, templates)\n2. How workflow graphs are currently rendered\n3. The current layout engine/approach for workflow visualization\n4. Any existing graph/layout related code\n\nSearch thoroughly for:\n- Web UI templates, HTML files, JavaScript files\n- Graph rendering code, SVG generation\n- Workflow visualization code\n- Layout engine code\n- Any references to \"graph\", \"layout\", \"workflow\" in web-related files\n\nBe very thorough - check cmd/, internal/, web/, ui/, static/, templates/, and any other directories.","agentId":"aae3c1247625e8c29","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have a complete understanding of the web UI code. Let me create a comprehensive final report.\n\n## Web UI Exploration Report - Cloche Project\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's a comprehensive summary of the web UI code structure and workflow visualization:\n\n### 1. **Web UI File Locations**\n\n**Directory Structure:**\n```\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/\n├── handler.go              (Main web server - 1,300+ lines)\n├── handler_stream_test.go\n├── handler_test.go\n├── static/\n│   └── style.css          (600 lines, complete styling)\n└── templates/\n    ├── layout.html         (Master template - 20 lines)\n    ├── projects.html       (Projects overview 